Aim
To implement light and dark mode functionality.

Algorithm
STEP 1 : Create the basic HTML structure for the webpage. 
STEP 2 : Define CSS variables for theme colors. 
STEP 3 : Create a dark theme using data attributes. 
STEP 4 : Apply base styles using CSS variables. 
STEP 5 : Add a theme toggle button.
STEP 6 : Write JavaScript to detect the current theme. 
STEP 7 : Toggle between light and dark mode. 
STEP 8 : Apply smooth transition effects. 
STEP 9 : Test the theme toggle functionality.


<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8" />
  <title>Dark / Light Mode</title>

  <style>
    /* ===== THEME VARIABLES ===== */
    :root {
      --bg-color: #f4f6f8;
      --text-color: #111827;
      --card-bg: #ffffff;
      --border-color: #e5e7eb;
      --button-bg: #111827;
      --button-text: #ffffff;
    }

    [data-theme="dark"] {
      --bg-color: #0f172a;
      --text-color: #e5e7eb;
      --card-bg: #1e293b;
      --border-color: #334155;
      --button-bg: #e5e7eb;
      --button-text: #111827;
    }

    /* ===== BASE STYLES ===== */
    * {
      margin: 0;
      padding: 0;
      box-sizing: border-box;
    }

    body {
      font-family: Inter, Arial, sans-serif;
      background: var(--bg-color);
      color: var(--text-color);
      min-height: 100vh;
      display: grid;
      place-items: center;
      transition: background 0.3s, color 0.3s;
    }

    .container {
      background: var(--card-bg);
      padding: 32px;
      border-radius: 12px;
      border: 1px solid var(--border-color);
      width: 320px;
      text-align: center;
      transition: background 0.3s, border 0.3s;
    }

    h1 {
      margin-bottom: 16px;
    }

    p {
      margin-bottom: 24px;
      font-size: 14px;
      opacity: 0.8;
    }

    button {
      padding: 10px 16px;
      border-radius: 8px;
      border: none;
      background: var(--button-bg);
      color: var(--button-text);
      cursor: pointer;
      font-weight: 600;
      transition: background 0.3s, color 0.3s;
    }
  </style>
</head>

<body>
  <div class="container">
    <h1>Theme Toggle</h1>
    <p>Click the button to switch between Light and Dark mode.</p>
    <button id="toggleTheme">Toggle Theme</button>
  </div>

  <script>
    const toggleBtn = document.getElementById("toggleTheme");
    const body = document.body;

    toggleBtn.addEventListener("click", () => {
      const currentTheme = body.getAttribute("data-theme");

      if (currentTheme === "dark") {
        body.removeAttribute("data-theme");
      } else {
        body.setAttribute("data-theme", "dark");
      }
    });
  </script>
</body>
</html>
